HEADWORD: Dicrotism
<hw>Di"cro*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A condition in which there are two beats or waves of the arterial
pulse to each beat of the heart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

